SIMPLE: sadness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sadness
<hw>Sad"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Heaviness;
firmness.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Seriousness; gravity; discretion.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her <qex>sadness</qex> and her benignity.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Quality of being sad, or unhappy; gloominess;
sorrowfulness; dejection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dim <qex>sadness</qex> did not spare⟦br⟧
That time celestial visages.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Sorrow; heaviness; dejection. See
<er>Grief</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sadr</ent>⟦br⟧
